THe voice note was very satisfactory but the video quality and illustration were poor;  not every said instruction was detailed in the video and that made it very difficult for me to follow through. Also, the Cloud Workspace kept refusing to display the next webpage for me to carrry out my guided project and my cloud workspace expired due to time wasted as a result of the cloud workspace malfunctioning all through the voice note. Once this is rectified, it will help others you wants to learn how to use figma.

E​xtremely basic as you might expect from the length and title. Very poorly narrated but that's not the end of the world. What is more concerning is that basic and helpful things like navigating around the page, zooming in and out, using components from a team library etc are not covered.
Because you haven't touched figma in the way that should be explained I would like to give you a 3 out of 5 starts in your course

The websites in the Workspace were constantly getting errors and having to be reloaded. The video does not match up with the current Figma program which makes it hard to follow along. The issues made this project take a lot longer than the estimated time and then it told me my time for using the Workspace had run out and I couldn't continue using the workspace at all. I also did not like the tone and pace of the voiceover. It was hard to pay attention and the actions often did not line up with the movements of the video. The video also used slides to show the screens instead of actually navigating the site, so that also made it harder to follow and learn how to navigate the program.
